# Skeletor 💀

**A deep codebase understanding and architecture visualization tool.**

[![Python 3.10+](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.10+-blue.svg)](https://www.python.org/downloads/)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)
[![Tests](https://img.shields.io/badge/tests-passing-brightgreen.svg)]()

Skeletor analyzes your codebase and automatically generates Interactive Dashboards, Mermaid architecture diagrams, and Code Complexity metrics. Stop guessing how your legacy code is connected, and let Skeletor build the map.

## 🚀 Features

- **Multi-Language AST Parsing**: Powered by `tree-sitter` for 100% accurate extraction of classes, functions, and imports.
- **Dependency Graphing**: Builds a directed graph of your codebase to understand exactly what relies on what.
- **Layer Detection**: Automatically categorizes files into architectural layers (Controllers, Services, Repositories, Models).
- **Code Health Metrics**: Identifies **Dead Code**, **Hotspots** (high coupling), and **Circular Dependencies**.
- **Visual Dashboards**: Exports an interactive D3 + Mermaid.js HTML dashboard.
- **MCP Server Support**: Connects natively to AI Agents (Claude Code, Antigravity) via the Model Context Protocol.

## 📦 Installation

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/skeletor.git
cd skeletor

# Install via pip
pip install -e .
```

## 🛠️ Usage

### 1. Command Line Interface (CLI)
Analyze a codebase by simply pointing Skeletor at a directory:

```bash
python -m skeletor /path/to/your/project
```

Skeletor will output a `skeletor-out/` directory containing:
- `ARCHITECTURE_REPORT.md`: A beautiful markdown summary of code health.
- `dashboard.html`: An interactive web UI visualizing the architecture.
- `model.json`: Raw graph node/edge data.
- `*.mmd`: Standalone Mermaid diagram files.

### 2. AI Agent Integration (Antigravity & Claude Code)
Skeletor provides a pre-configured Skill profile allowing AI agents to run deep architectural scans autonomously.

#### As an Agent Skill
If you want your agent to use Skeletor, just make sure the `SKILL.md` file is in your agent's skill directory:

**For Antigravity (Global Setup):**
```bash
# Windows
mkdir -p %USERPROFILE%\.gemini\config\skills\skeletor
copy .agents\skills\skeletor\SKILL.md %USERPROFILE%\.gemini\config\skills\skeletor\

# macOS/Linux
mkdir -p ~/.gemini/config/skills/skeletor
cp .agents/skills/skeletor/SKILL.md ~/.gemini/config/skills/skeletor/
```

**For Claude Code (Project Setup):**
Claude Code automatically discovers skills in the `.agents/skills/` directory. If you commit `.agents/skills/skeletor/SKILL.md` to your repository, Claude Code will automatically be able to use Skeletor to analyze your project!

### 3. Model Context Protocol (MCP) Server
You can also hook Skeletor into any MCP-compatible client:
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "skeletor": {
      "command": "python",
      "args": ["-c", "import skeletor.serve; skeletor.serve.start_server()"]
    }
  }
}
```

## 🧠 How it Works (The 8-Stage Pipeline)

1. **Scan**: Smartly discovers files while ignoring `.gitignore` and `.env` secrets.
2. **Parse**: Uses multi-language ASTs to extract structural tokens.
3. **Model**: Links tokens into a unified Directed Graph (DiGraph).
4. **Layer**: Heuristically detects MVC / Layered architecture boundaries.
5. **Analyze**: Computes coupling, cohesion, and dead code metrics.
6. **Diagram**: Generates structural Mermaid.js visualizations.
7. **Report**: Synthesizes a Markdown audit.
8. **Export**: Renders the HTML Dashboard.

